{"type":"session_message","session_id":"ses_28c6e0507ffeaXxTAMFtC4gCYu","role":"assistant","message_id":"msg_d739214bd001TsAAWaaPqnQ3j7","parts":[{"id":"prt_d73921dca0014k7kEo9HIqxkW6","messageID":"msg_d739214bd001TsAAWaaPqnQ3j7","sessionID":"ses_28c6e0507ffeaXxTAMFtC4gCYu","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_c0245a4dae41457591fd558b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/workspace/README.md"},"output":"<path>/workspace/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>1: # Poetry: Python packaging and dependency management made easy\n2: \n3: [![Poetry](https://img.shields.io/endpoint?url=https://python-poetry.org/badge/v0.json)](https://python-poetry.org/)\n4: [![Stable Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/poetry?label=stable)][PyPI Releases]\n5: [![Pre-release Version](https://img.shields.io/github/v/release/python-poetry/poetry?label=pre-release&include_prereleases&sort=semver)][PyPI Releases]\n6: [![Python Versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/poetry)][PyPI]\n7: [![Download Stats](https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/poetry)](https://pypistats.org/packages/poetry)\n8: [![Discord](https://img.shields.io/discord/487711540787675139?logo=discord)][Discord]\n9: \n10: Poetry helps you declare, manage and install dependencies of Python projects,\n11: ensuring you have the right stack everywhere.\n12: \n13: ![Poetry Install](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/python-poetry/poetry/main/assets/install.gif)\n14: \n15: Poetry replaces `setup.py`, `requirements.txt`, `setup.cfg`, `MANIFEST.in` and `Pipfile` with a simple `pyproject.toml`\n16: based project format.\n17: \n18: ```toml\n19: [build-system]\n20: requires = [\"poetry-core>=2.0.0,<3.0.0\"]\n21: build-backend = \"poetry.core.masonry.api\"\n22: \n23: [project]\n24: name = \"my-package\"\n25: version = \"0.1.0\"\n26: description = \"The description of the package\"\n27: readme = \"README.md\"\n28: \n29: license = \"MIT\"\n30: license-files = [\"LICENSE\"]\n31: \n32: # No Python upper bound for package metadata\n33: requires-python = \">=3.9\"\n34: \n35: authors = [\n36:     { name = \"Sébastien Eustace\", email = \"sebastien@eustace.io\" },\n37: ]\n38: \n39: # Keywords (translated to tags on the package index)\n40: keywords = [\"packaging\", \"poetry\"]\n41: \n42: dependencies = [\n43:     # equivalent to ^3.8.1 with semver constraints\n44:     \"aiohttp (>=3.8.1,<4.0.0)\",\n45:     # dependency with extras\n46:     \"requests[security] (>=2.28,<3.0)\",\n47:     # version-specific dependency with prereleases allowed (see below)\n48:     \"tomli (>=2.0.1,<3.0.0) ; python_version < '3.11'\",\n49:     # git dependency with branch specified\n50:     \"cleo @ git+https://github.com/python-poetry/cleo.git@main\",\n51: ]\n52: \n53: [project.urls]\n54: repository = \"https://github.com/python-poetry/poetry\"\n55: homepage = \"https://python-poetry.org\"\n56: \n57: # Scripts are easily expressed\n58: [project.scripts]\n59: my_package_cli = \"my_package.console:run\"\n60: \n61: [project.optional-dependencies]\n62: # optional dependency to be installed via 'poetry install -E my-extra'\n63: my-extra = [\"pendulum (>=3.1.0,<4.0.0)\"]\n64: \n65: [tool.poetry.dependencies]\n66: # Python upper bound for locking\n67: python = \">=3.9,<4.0\"\n68: # Version-specific dependencies with prereleases allowed\n69: tomli = { allow-prereleases = true }\n70: \n71: # Dependency groups are supported for organizing your dependencies\n72: [dependency-groups]\n73: dev = [\"pytest (>=7.1.2,<8.0.0)\", \"pytest-cov (>=3.0,<4.0)\"]\n74: docs = [\"Sphinx (>=5.1.1,<6.0.0)\"]\n75: \n76: # ...and can be installed only when explicitly requested\n77: # via 'poetry install --with docs'\n78: [tool.poetry.group.docs]\n79: optional = true\n80: \n81: # Alternatively, you can use Poetry specific syntax\n82: # to specify dependency groups\n83: [tool.poetry.group.lint]\n84: optional = true\n85: \n86: [tool.poetry.group.lint.dependencies]\n87: ruff = \">=0.10.0\"\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ## Installation\n91: \n92: Poetry supports multiple installation methods, including a simple script found at [install.python-poetry.org]. For full\n93: installation instructions, including advanced usage of the script, alternate install methods, and CI best practices, see\n94: the full [installation documentation].\n95: \n96: ## Documentation\n97: \n98: [Documentation] for the current version of Poetry (as well as the development branch and recently out of support\n99: versions) is available from the [official website].\n100: \n101: ## Contribute\n102: \n103: Poetry is a large, complex project always in need of contributors. For those new to the project, a list of\n104: [suggested issues] to work on in Poetry and poetry-core is available. The full [contributing documentation] also\n105: provides helpful guidance.\n106: \n107: ## Resources\n108: \n109: * [Releases][PyPI Releases]\n110: * [Official Website]\n111: * [Documentation]\n112: * [Issue Tracker]\n113: * [Discord]\n114: \n115:   [PyPI]: https://pypi.org/project/poetry/\n116:   [PyPI Releases]: https://pypi.org/project/poetry/#history\n117:   [Official Website]: https://python-poetry.org\n118:   [Documentation]: https://python-poetry.org/docs/\n119:   [Issue Tracker]: https://github.com/python-poetry/poetry/issues\n120:   [Suggested Issues]: https://github.com/python-poetry/poetry/contribute\n121:   [Contributing Documentation]: https://python-poetry.org/docs/contributing\n122:   [Discord]: https://discord.com/invite/awxPgve\n123:   [install.python-poetry.org]: https://install.python-poetry.org\n124:   [Installation Documentation]: https://python-poetry.org/docs/#installation\n125: \n126: ## Related Projects\n127: \n128: * [poetry-core](https://github.com/python-poetry/poetry-core): PEP 517 build-system for Poetry projects, and\n129: dependency-free core functionality of the Poetry frontend\n130: * [poetry-plugin-export](https://github.com/python-poetry/poetry-plugin-export): Export Poetry projects/lock files to\n131: foreign formats like requirements.txt\n132: * [poetry-plugin-bundle](https://github.com/python-poetry/poetry-plugin-bundle): Install Poetry projects/lock files to\n133: external formats like virtual environments\n134: * [install.python-poetry.org](https://github.com/python-poetry/install.python-poetry.org): The official Poetry\n135: installation script\n136: * [website](https://github.com/python-poetry/website): The official Poetry website and blog\n137: \n138: ## Supporters\n139: \n140: Thanks to [JetBrains](https://www.jetbrains.com) for supporting us with licenses for their tools.\n141: \n142: [<img src=\"https://resources.jetbrains.com/storage/products/company/brand/logos/jetbrains.svg\" width=\"150\" alt=\"JetBrains logo.\" />](https://www.jetbrains.com)\n\n(End of file - total 142 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Poetry: Python packaging and dependency management made easy\n\n[![Poetry](https://img.shields.io/endpoint?url=https://python-poetry.org/badge/v0.json)](https://python-poetry.org/)\n[![Stable Version](https://img.shields.io/pypi/v/poetry?label=stable)][PyPI Releases]\n[![Pre-release Version](https://img.shields.io/github/v/release/python-poetry/poetry?label=pre-release&include_prereleases&sort=semver)][PyPI Releases]\n[![Python Versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/poetry)][PyPI]\n[![Download Stats](https://img.shields.io/pypi/dm/poetry)](https://pypistats.org/packages/poetry)\n[![Discord](https://img.shields.io/discord/487711540787675139?logo=discord)][Discord]\n\nPoetry helps you declare, manage and install dependencies of Python projects,\nensuring you have the right stack everywhere.\n\n![Poetry Install](https://raw.githubusercontent.com/python-poetry/poetry/main/assets/install.gif)\n\nPoetry replaces `setup.py`, `requirements.txt`, `setup.cfg`, `MANIFEST.in` and `Pipfile` with a simple `pyproject.toml`\nbased project format.\n\n```toml\n[build-system]\nrequires = [\"poetry-core>=2.0.0,<3.0.0\"]","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"README.md","time":{"start":1775760449403,"end":1775760449412}}}]}
